In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and garlic; add meat. Seal bag and turn to coat; refrigerate for 4 hours, turning occasionally. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine horseradish sauce ingredients; cover and refrigerate. In another bowl, combine the tomato sauce, steak sauce and brown sugar; cover and refrigerate. Drain and discard marinade. Pat meat dry with paper towels. using one fondue pot for every six people, heat 2-3 cups oil in each pot to 375 degrees F. Use fondue forks to cook meat in oil until it reaches desired doneness. Serve with the horseradish and barbecue sauces.